UID:oMYLZg2TTYl6cc76BvAnM
SUMMARY:What AI\, Cybersecurity\, and Tequila Have in Common.
DTSTAMP:20260701T101458Z
DTSTART:20260707T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Register here: https://luma.com/0rfy7te0 \nMost companies treat
	 AI like a shortcut to growth: it delivers immediate results\, but the lon
	g-term operational fallout is brutal. \n​Everyone is caught up in the rush
	\, plugging automated tools into critical infrastructure without checking 
	the foundation. But speed without security isn’t progress\, it’s an open i
	nvitation for cyber threats. It’s time to face the structural reality. \n​
	Join Blue People and Alpfa Houston for an unfiltered session with Reynaldo
	 Gonzalez\, an industry veteran with 18+ years of experience securing crit
	ical infrastructure. \n​The Realities We’re Breaking Down: \n​AI doesn’t c
	hange the value of knowledge\; it changes the value of curiosity. The ulti
	mate security edge belongs to leaders who know how to ask the right questi
	ons\, not just trust the output. \n​Your biggest competitive advantage is 
	becoming more human\, not less. In a world of automated systems\, human ju
	dgment and sharp intuition remain the only truly un-hackable firewalls lef
	t. \n​AI is the greatest operational amplifier ever created. It scales you
	r wins\, but it weaponizes your internal flaws. If your baseline security 
	is weak\, AI just helps you fail faster and at scale. \n​The single bigges
	t risk today isn’t AI\, it’s human complacency. The danger isn’t rogue tec
	hnology or advanced malware\; it’s our own blind trust in automated workfl
	ows. \n​Stop operating on hope. Turn cyber resilience into your unfair adv
	antage. \n​📅 July 7th\, 2026 | 5:00 PM – 7:00 PM\n📍 The Ion Houston\nHoste
	d by Blue People & Alpfa Houston \n​👉 Ask about our parking options at the
	 end of the event!\n\nhttps://iondistrict.com/event/what-ai-cybersecurity-
	and-tequila-have-in-common/\n\nFrom Ion District
URL:https://iondistrict.com/event/what-ai-cybersecurity-and-tequila-have-in
	-common/
LOCATION:Ion\, 4201 Main Street\, Houston\, TX\, 77002\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:ion-district
CATEGORIES:Ion District
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
