UID:PcIsDiZxFu0Cdphp28Og1
SUMMARY:Japan Junction
DTSTAMP:20260701T101458Z
DTSTART:20260708T163000Z
DESCRIPTION:June 10: “The Tubmaker Who Flew to the Sea” and Teru Teru Bozu 
	paper craft \nJune in Japan is known as Tsuyu\, the rainy season\, when ge
	ntle rains and cloudy skies become a part of daily life. But what do you d
	o when you are hoping for sunny weather before an important day? \nIn Japa
	n\, people often hang Teru Teru Bozu\, a traditional handmade decoration b
	elieved to bring good weather. Usually made from tissue paper or cloth\, t
	hese cheerful little figures are displayed near windows or doors to wish f
	or sunshine. \nJoin us for a kamishibai reading of “Okeya no Ten Nobori” o
	r “The Tubmaker Who Flew to the Sky\,” a whimsical tale featuring a sleepy
	 thunder god\, Kaminari-sama\, whose storms bring rainy weather. \nAfter t
	he story\, make your own Teru Teru Bozu out of craft paper to chase away t
	he rain and Kaminari-sama and invite sunny skies!\n\nhttps://www.levyparkh
	ouston.org/events/japan-junction-3-2-2-2/2026-07-08/\n\nFrom Levy Park Hou
	ston
URL:https://www.levyparkhouston.org/events/japan-junction-3-2-2-2/2026-07-0
	8/
LOCATION:Levy Park (Event Pavilion)\, TX
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:levy-park-houston
CATEGORIES:Levy Park Houston
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
