 6/Banner.jpg
UID:GqWFM9TqQCZepm1mSAFwF
SUMMARY:Houston Comic Exchange II
DTSTAMP:20260701T101459Z
DTSTART:20260801T100000Z
DESCRIPTION:Houston Comic Exchange II – Built for Comic Collectors\nSummer 
	is prime comic-hunting season\, and CCS Houston Comic Exchange II brings t
	ogether collectors\, dealers\, and fans for a day of buying\, selling\, tr
	ading\, and discovering comics. From key issues and first appearances to h
	idden gems and box-fresh finds\, every table offers something worth diggin
	g for. \nNo gatekeeping\, no pressure\, just comics and the people who lov
	e them. \n  \n📅 Saturday\, August 1\, 2026 | 10AM – 5PM \n📍 9700 Bissonnet
	 St\, Unit 1500\, Houston\, TX \n🎟️ FREE Entry + FREE Parking \n  \n🔥 Event
	 Highlights 🔥\n📦 50 Vendor Tables – All Comics\, All Formats \nSingles\, b
	ack issues\, key issues\, first appearances\, graded slabs\, raw runs\, in
	die and small press\, variant covers. Vendor tables dedicated entirely to 
	comics\, no toys\, no filler. If you’re a comic collector\, this floor was
	 built for you. \n  \n🔍 Key Issues and First Appearances \nThis is where t
	he hunt lives. Vendors bring the deep cuts\, raw back issues worth digging
	 through\, graded books if you’re chasing condition\, and the kind of keys
	 that actually show up when serious collectors are clearing their own coll
	ections to make room. \n  \n📚 Back-Issue Digging and Indie Discovery \nNot
	 every great find is a grail. Long boxes of back issues across decades and
	 publishers\, plus indie comics and small press titles that never make it 
	to a standard shop shelf. Come with a list or come ready to browse – both 
	work. \n  \n🤝 Vendors Who Collect Too \nThe people behind these tables are
	 the same people who will ask what you’re hunting before they start pullin
	g books for you. The Houston Comic Exchange is a community floor first. Th
	e conversations are part of the event. \n  \n🛒 Vendor Table Applications \
	nHouston comic vendors: we’re gathering a focused comics-only crowd\, and 
	free entry is driving serious foot traffic. Apply for your table here 👉🏻 ht
	tps://forms.gle/7q6pjcoiJTPbJouP8 \n  \nThe key issue you’ve been tracking
	 is probably in one of those long boxes this summer. The Houston Comic Exc
	hange II\, August 1. Free entry\, free parking\, always.\n\nhttps://ccs-ho
	uston.com/events/houston-comic-exchange-ii/\n\nFrom CCS Houston
URL:https://ccs-houston.com/events/houston-comic-exchange-ii/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:ccs-houston
CATEGORIES:CCS Houston
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
