 ntent/uploads/Meredith-Willsons-The-Music-Man-new-ftr-Image.jpg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.tuts.org/wp-content/uploads/Meredith-
 Willsons-The-Music-Man-new-ftr-Image.jpg
UID:5ZpeRj4MXYWfU9u0qHn52
SUMMARY:The Music Man
DTSTAMP:20260701T101500Z
DTSTART:20260915T080000Z
DESCRIPTION:Seventy-six trombones. One unforgettable musical!\n			\n				\n	
				\n				\n				\n				Meredith Willson’s six-time Tony Award®-winning belov
	ed musical comedy The Music Man marches into Houston with laughter\, heart
	\, and all the music you love. Following the fast-talking traveling salesm
	an Harold Hill as he cons the people of River City\, Iowa\, into buying in
	struments and uniforms for a boys’ band that he vows to organize. Featurin
	g songs such as “Seventy-Six Trombones\,” “Trouble\,” “’Till There Was You
	\,” “Pick-a-Little\,” and “Gary\, Indiana\,” The Music Man is a classic mu
	sical to be shared with every generation. \n			\n			\n				\n				\n				\n		
			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n			\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n
				\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				
	\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				CRITICAL ACCLAIM FOR
	 THE MUSIC MAN\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n					\n			\
	n			\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n					\n			\n			\n			\
	n					– The Telegraph \n					\n					“A joyous\, blissful Broadway event!” 
	\n					\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n					\
	n			\n			\n			\n					– Variety \n					\n					“Grand and Glorious!” “…total
	ly enchanting abso-tootin’-lutely smashing revival. It will give you new l
	ife.” \n					\n				\n				\n			\n			\n				\n			\n			\n				\n				\n				\n			
		\n			\n				\n				\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n	
				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				PERFORMANCE SCHED
	ULE\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				\n					\n				\n				\n			
		\n				\n				Tuesday\, Sept 15\, 7:30 p.m. – H-E-B Community Night\n			\n
					\n				\n				\n				\n				Wednesday\, Sept 16\, 7:30 p.m. \n			\n				\n
					\n				\n				\n				Thursday\, Sept 17\, 7:30 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n	
				\n				\n				Friday\, Sept 18\, 8 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n	
				Saturday\, Sept 19\, 2 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				Saturd
	ay\, Sept 19\, 8 p.m.\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				Sunday\, Sept 20\
	, 2 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				Sunday\, Sept 20\, 7:30 p.m. 
	\n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n				Tuesday\, Sept 22\, 7:30 p.m. \n			\n	
				\n				\n				\n				\n				Wednesday\, Sept 23\, 7:30 p.m. \n			\n				\n	
				\n				\n				\n				Thursday\, Sept 24\, 7:30 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n		
			\n				\n				Friday\, Sept 25\, 8 p.m. \n			\n				\n				\n				\n				\n		
